The cross-validation results in Figure 2 show that the larger model does improve out-of-sample prediction, but only modestly. In this run, the mean RMSE decreased from about 0.066 for the selected three-predictor model to about 0.058 for the larger five-predictor model. That is a real predictive gain, but it is not dramatic, so the trade-off between predictive improvement and interpretability still needs to be judged explicitly.

